      <h4>Name: Saline Tester.</h4>
      <p>
        <strong>Manufacture:</strong> CPR, Produktions-und Vertriebs GmbH, Germany.
        <strong>Description:</strong> This machine tests condoms for pinholes according to ISO 4074:2002.
        The inside of the condoms having been filled with conductive salt water, the condoms are dipped into a saltwater basin. The voltage between the electrodes in the two saline solutions is then measured. The intact latex film of the condom is an insulator. If the latex film has a hole, an electricity flow will be measured, and the hole will thus be detected.
        The machine can test 10 condoms simultaneously, and its computer can be connected to a network server.
      </p>
